            <Paragraph FontSize="22"><Run>How to: Position Tabs on a TabControl</Run>

            </Paragraph>

          </TableCell>

        </TableRow>

      </TableRowGroup>

    </Table>

    <Paragraph>This example shows how to create a TabControl and specify the placement of its tabs. You can place tabs at the top, bottom, left, or right of the control. The example specifies tab placement by setting the TabStripPlacement property. 
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph>The following example creates a <Run FontWeight="Bold">TabControl</Run>
 by using Extensible Application Markup Language (XAML). It positions the tabs on the left side. 
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22">Example
    </Paragraph>

    <Table CellSpacing="5">
      <TableRowGroup>
        <TableRow>
          <TableCell>
            <Paragraph FontSize="22"><Run>XAML </Run>

            </Paragraph>

          </TableCell>

        </TableRow>

        <TableRow>
          <TableCell>
            <Paragraph xml:space="preserve" TextAlignment="Left" FontSize="8pt" FontFamily="Courier New"><Run>
&lt;TabControl TabStripPlacement="Left" Margin="0, 0, 0, 10"> 
&lt;TabItem Name="fontweight" Header="FontWeight"> 
&lt;TabItem.Content>
&lt;TextBlock TextWrapping="WrapWithOverflow"> FontWeight property information goes here.
&lt;/TextBlock>
&lt;/TabItem.Content> 
&lt;/TabItem> 
&lt;TabItem Name="fontsize" Header="FontSize"> 
&lt;TabItem.Content>
&lt;TextBlock TextWrapping="WrapWithOverflow"> FontSize property information goes here.
&lt;/TextBlock>
&lt;/TabItem.Content> 
&lt;/TabItem> 
&lt;/TabControl> </Run>

            </Paragraph>

          </TableCell>

        </TableRow>

      </TableRowGroup>

    </Table>

    <Paragraph>For the complete sample, see Tab Control Sample.
    </Paragraph>

